# Blunno PWA rules

- `app/manifest.ts` defines the installable manifest and `/app` start URL.
- `scripts/generate-sw.mjs` generates `public/sw.js` after `next build`.
- `scripts/generate-precache-manifest.mjs` generates `public/precache-manifest.json` from routes, build assets, icons, and media.
- `src/components/shared/ServiceWorkerRegister.tsx` registers the worker in production.
- Bump `scripts/offline-version.mjs` for cache-breaking releases.
- Keep `/offline` as the navigation fallback and keep the documented core routes precached.
- Do not hand-edit generated service worker or precache output when the template or generator is the source of truth.

Run the full release gate with `npm run verify`; it creates the production PWA assets once and exercises offline behavior through Playwright.
